---
title: "Writing a Systematic Review"
---

# What is a Systematic Review?

Def.: A systamtic review summarizes existing research in order to answer a research question. It is a systematic, transparent approach to collect and interpret all existing research on that specific question.

| Type of Research Synthesis | Narrative Review | Systematic Review | Meta-Analysis |
|------------------|------------------|------------------|------------------|
| Type of Research | Secondary Research | Secondary Research | Secondary Research |
| Aim | Summarizes a research field; who did what? Identifies gaps and tensions. | Answers a research question | Answers a research question |
| Method of Analysis | Narrative summary | Collection, interpretation, and synthesis of research | Statistical procedure |


